Web page: https://www.univie.ac.at/tops/Period04/
Requirements: Java Runtime Environment (JRE)

To install a JRE on Ubuntu use the following commands:
sudo apt update
sudo apt install default-jre

Download the period04 installer using wget:
wget https://www.univie.ac.at/tops/Period04/files/v120/period04-v1.2.0-linux-64bit.sh
Run the installer like this:
sh period04-v1.2.0-linux-64bit.sh
Accept the default installation locations.
The installer will create a directory "bin" in your the top level of your home directory.
Either add "${HOME}/bin" to your $PATH like this:
echo 'export PATH="${HOME}/bin:${PATH}"' | tee -a ${HOME}/.bashrc
Or run the program with this command:
~/bin/period04
